Avian Influenza: What Pet Owners and Veterinarians Need to Know
Highly pathogenic avian influenza (HPAI) has made headlines following a surge of cases recently. Wild birds and poultry flocks have been significantly affected, as have dairy cows, goats, and pets, including cats, dogs, ferrets, and more.

Avian Influenza
Influenza A viruses are divided into 16 hemagglutinin (H1-16) and 9 neuraminidase (N1-9) subtypes. Which of the following subtypes is most likely to cause a highly pathogenic form of avian influenza in poultry?
